LAGOS , September 13 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- Mali 's President Alpha Konare has held separate talks with his counterparts of Guinea and Liberia in a shuttle diplomacy to ease tensions between the two West African countries , reports reaching here said on Wednesday .
Konare , also current chairman of the Economic Community of West African States -LRB- ECOWAS -RRB- , said in a statement following the talks held on Tuesday , the two leaders had undertaken to cooperate with the sub-regional body to prevent their disputes from escalating .
Mali 's president first flew to the Liberian capital Monrovia to hold a closed-door meeting with Liberian President Charles Taylor , which was followed his journey to the Guinean capital Konakry for talks with his Guinean counterpart Lansana Conte , the report said .
Liberia and Guinea have repeatedly accused each other of harboring rebels fighting their respective governments in the cross-border attacks .
Guinea said lately that armed groups along its borders with Liberia and Sierra Leone had launched attacks into its territory during the past two weeks , killing about 80 people .
According to a separate report , Conte on Tuesday also held talks with visiting Sierra Leonean President Tejan Kabbah over the refugee crisis between the two countries .
<ENAMEX TYPE="OKAY">Kabbah said after the talks that he had been assured by his Guinean counterpart of the safety of Sierra Leonean refugees in Guinea</ENAMEX> , adding that both sides had agreed to do everything to prevent the destabilization of each other .
